Sasarin burst forth in flames, this towering slark person ignited a small patch of forest, then circled above, observing the timing.  It was strange, however, that when he slowed down, the strange cries behind him also stopped. Sasarin had forgotten that there was a passenger on his back.
"Please, Tenruk, you haven't turned into a slark person before?"
"Being taken by a giant pink dragon while flying is a different matter!"
"Is everything okay, Kayel?"
Kayel seemed to disagree with Nisi's words, he looked paler than usual, his claws had deeply dug into Sasarin's back, drawing blood from the slark person, but Sasarin seemed to not care.  Nevertheless, Sasarin realized that he had scared his new friend, so he found an empty space to land.
"Sorry, sorry, I can smell something. I have to take care of it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tunku crawled down from Ssarlin's back and slid down the tail to the ground, asking sharply. "We left Rettwick behind! We abandoned that strong and fierce guy! How is he going to find us?"
"He'll figure it out... " Nisec clicked her tongue. "Rettwick is slow to react, but not dumb."
"Can Rettwick drive?"
Nisec blinked her eyes and turned to look at Tunku. "Of course, he can drive."
“Have you ever seen Rettvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a car like Kayel's either. He only rides a bike to work because you always drive us to school. He only has one bicycle.”
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin burst out laughing uncontrollably, but no one knew what he was laughing about. Sasalin remained calm for quite some time.
“Sorry, sorry, I just imagined something. Your big friend wearing armor, riding a small bicycle designed for children of Temsen. The image is too funny! I wish I had telepathic abilities. This idea is too interesting! I have to remember it well!”
Kayel also laughed because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. “Okay, okay. But what did you smell, and why did you fly so fast?”
Sasalin whistled, then quickly disappeared after flying, and flew back to drop a body in front of Nici. It was an Aurosarak, a very rare gold-white dragon-like species. However, its head was missing. “Another one died. I heard their cries. I smelled their blood. I must protect them, hunt down the killer. This is the will of Izi. Those creatures are nearby.”
A powerful slork suddenly froze. Nixi and Kael were also frozen, their attention drawn to a gap on the outskirts of the open field. A massive, pitch-black thing was staring at them, making a hissing sound. It suddenly spread its enormous, dark wings and charged forward, aiming straight for Sazalin, completely ignoring the three small creatures between it and Sazalin. Kael and Tenruk barely managed to dodge to the side, but Nixi found herself flung to the ground, almost landing on Sazalin.
Sazalin grabbed Nixi and flung her onto its back, using its long and agile tail to do so. Then it took off into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly gave chase.
Kael clicked his tongue and pulled out a rifle from behind, then opened a bag and pulled out a belt of bullets. He hung the belt across his chest for easy access, but soon realized that Nixi, Sazalin, and the creature were nowhere to be seen.
“Hey, Tenruk, can you turn into a flying animal?” Kael asked.
“You want to chase after them?”
"Waste of words."
"But....one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? I've got a powerful rifle in my hand, and I can fire at any time. All I need is to see it, and I can take it down."
Tenuk hesitated for a moment, then stepped back a step, leaving some space for himself. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenuk's body stretched out, its fur turned into scales, its arms turned into wings. He soon transformed into a normal, light blue Slark, but his eyes remained red.
"Come on."
Now Tenno looks like a fairly ordinary Slark, with plates on his back lined up neatly, and a pair of spikes growing out, making it easier for Kael to grab onto him. Tenno took a long time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly adjusted his course and chased after.
However, Tenno and Kael soon realized they weren't the only ones with an opponent. A second dark creature emerged from beneath them, and Tenno barely dodged the impact.
"I guess this must be the other terrifying big monster Rannix was worried about?" Kael furrowed his brow, trying to fire at the second monster, but he missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tennu didn't respond, he was busy flying towards Nixi and Sazali, despite the other monster chasing after them. Kael clumsily turned around, facing the monster. The monster was chasing after them, and Kael thought it was good news because it would be easier for him to aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it let out a pained roar before disappearing into the forest. Kael wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he thought it was definitely lagging behind.
In front, Sazali was frantically waving his body, spewing out flames at the dark monster, while Nixi desperately grabbed onto Sazali to prevent him from falling. Although this monster was definitely injured, it seemed to be enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs seemed to have caused little damage. After Sazali stabilized his body, Nixi took out a trusted shotgun. Of course, the shotgun wouldn't be able to handle this kind of monster, but at the very least, the scattered bullets could scare off this black beast?
